The paper deals with constructions of linear codes and their applications in secret sharing and communication over quantum channels. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of multivariate polynomials and Cartesian product point sets also suggests a possible connection to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the Feng-Rao bounds, which are related to coding theory and error-correcting codes, indicating a possible connection to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
